Class AbstractPackageManagerClient

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.adamcin.granite.client.packman.AbstractPackageManagerClient

    PackageManagerClient
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AsyncPackageManagerClient, Http3PackageManagerClient, Http4PackageManagerClient

    public abstract class AbstractPackageManagerClient
extends Object
implements PackageManagerClient
    The AbstractPackageManagerClient provides constants and concrete implementations for generic method logic and response handling.

      • checkServiceAvailability

        protected abstract AbstractPackageManagerClient.Either<? extends Exception,Boolean> checkServiceAvailability(boolean checkTimeout,
                                                                                                             long timeoutRemaining)
        The CRX PackageManagerServlet does not support GET requests. The only use for GET is to check service availability. If anything other than 401 or 405 is returned, the service should be considered unavailable.
        Parameters:
        checkTimeout - set to true to enforce a timeout
        timeoutRemaining - remaining timeout in milliseconds
        Returns:
        either a throwable or a boolean
